    stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;
    stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;
    &lt;line x1=&#34;4&#34; y1=&#34;9&#34; x2=&#34;20&#34; y2=&#34;9&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;4&#34; y1=&#34;15&#34; x2=&#34;20&#34; y2=&#34;15&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;10&#34; y1=&#34;3&#34; x2=&#34;8&#34; y2=&#34;21&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;16&#34; y1=&#34;3&#34; x2=&#34;14&#34; y2=&#34;21&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;

&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;




&lt;h4 class=&#34;header-anchor-wrapper&#34;&gt;Et two?
  &lt;a href=&#34;#et-two&#34; class=&#34;header-anchor-link&#34;&gt;
&lt;svg
    xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;
    width=&#34;1rem&#34; height=&#34;1rem&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;
    stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;
    stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;
    &lt;line x1=&#34;4&#34; y1=&#34;9&#34; x2=&#34;20&#34; y2=&#34;9&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;4&#34; y1=&#34;15&#34; x2=&#34;20&#34; y2=&#34;15&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;10&#34; y1=&#34;3&#34; x2=&#34;8&#34; y2=&#34;21&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;16&#34; y1=&#34;3&#34; x2=&#34;14&#34; y2=&#34;21&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;

&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is no rhyme or reason to the volume structure here other than I like counting things and it builds in breaks I can take basically whenever. Baseball was starting, thus ending Vol. 1 so I could do some fantasy drafting and watch a lot of games. But that’s all done, and after &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.mlb.com/news/blue-jays-no-hit-by-ronel-blanco-astros&#34;&gt;yesterday&lt;/a&gt; I may never watch another baseball game again anyway, so let’s get on with number two.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
